  <text>
      <body>
         <p>Isis to RC.
            your request, my love, was not neglected. I sent for the newspaper a little after eight, but had not an opportunity of sending it to you. David and Thomas being busy engaged with the Isis, which did not arrive untill late, and not untill after giving Thomas two j[ournies?]. Divine Providence has certainly been in our favour this eveg and next to you i place upon it, all my reliance: you must endeavour to write me a pretty love letter, that i can answer, i have a thousand endearing expressions, almost thrusting themselves upon my paper, but time will not just now permit me to give them utterance. [[2]]
            Believe me my beloved Richard, that my regard for you encreases [sic] every day, if possible every hour and the idea that i can without fear candidly tell you so adds no little to my happiness. adieu!
            Goodnight. I see in my mind, eye, and kiss, that high polished brow! May every wish of your heart be very soon attained.</p>
